RACE.RACE_TEXT: PIMLICO RACE 11 1M Turf CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 34280. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $16,000, allowed 4 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course , it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth).

CLAIM.OWNER: C and B Stables and Naylor David

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GILDA'S GIRL , patiently rated inside horses down the backstretch, began to advance leaving the turn, bumped with GATHER THE FACTS when going to the three path entering the stretch, swept to command in upper stretch and held sway under steady handling. OPINIONATED , unhurried down the backstretch, worked between horses through the stretch and rallied. STAGE CALL , steadied in close quarters leaving the starting gate, swung to the six path in upper stretch and rallied nicely. MILLROSE hugged the inner rail, disputed the pace and weakened the final furlong. TRES MARIA'S DREAM lacked speed, raced near the inner rail to mid stretch, steadied lacking room near the eighth pole and had insufficient time to recover. LEM ME DRINK raced in mid pack down the backstretch, was four deep on the far turn, got bumped by GATHER THE FACTS when that one came out after bumping with the winner at the head of the lane then flattened out. GATHER THE FACTS , a forward factor along the inner rail down the backstretch, eased out entering the far turn, bumped with the winner turning for home and weakened. KELLY'S PARTY GIRL was not a factor. SPOILS OF WAR , three wide both turns, gave way. NO SHARING , four wide the far turn, was not a factor. FORGOTTEN GIFT disputed the pace two wide and gave way. TWO SPOT chased the pace down the backstretch and faltered.
